body:
# Nginx Configuration

Nginx configuration is a declarative language using nested blocks of directives. Every change requires a syntax check (`nginx -t`) and reload (`nginx -s reload`) to take effect.

## Config File Locations

```bash
# Main config
/etc/nginx/nginx.conf

# Drop-in configs (recommended for per-site configs)
/etc/nginx/conf.d/*.conf

# Debian/Ubuntu sites model
/etc/nginx/sites-available/   # all configs
/etc/nginx/sites-enabled/     # symlinks to active configs
```

## Configuration Structure

```nginx
# Main context — global settings
worker_processes auto;
error_log /var/log/nginx/error.log warn;
pid /var/run/nginx.pid;

events {
    worker_connections 1024;
}

http {
    include /etc/nginx/mime.types;
    default_type application/octet-stream;

    # Logging
    log_format main '$remote_addr - $remote_user [$time_local] '
                    '"$request" $status $body_bytes_sent '
                    '"$http_referer" "$http_user_agent"';
    access_log /var/log/nginx/access.log main;

    # Performance
    sendfile on;
    tcp_nopush on;
    keepalive_timeout 65;
    gzip on;

    # Include site configs
    include /etc/nginx/conf.d/*.conf;
}
```

## Server Blocks

Each `server` block defines a virtual host:

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    listen [::]:80;           # IPv6
    server_name example.com www.example.com;

    root /var/www/example.com;
    index index.html;

    # Static files
    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ =404;
    }

    # API proxy
    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3000;
    }

    # Static assets with caching
    location ~* \.(css|js|png|jpg|jpeg|gif|ico|svg|woff2)$ {
        expires 30d;
        add_header Cache-Control "public, immutable";
    }

    # Deny dotfiles
    location ~ /\. {
        deny all;
    }
}
```

## Location Matching Priority

| Modifier | Type | Priority | Behavior |
|----------|------|----------|----------|
| `=`      | Exact | 1 (highest) | Exact URI match, stops search |
| `^~`     | Prefix | 2 | Longest prefix, skips regex |
| `~`      | Regex | 3 | Case-sensitive regex, first match |
| `~*`     | Regex | 3 | Case-insensitive regex, first match |
| (none)   | Prefix | 4 (lowest) | Longest prefix match |

## Directive Inheritance

Directives set at a higher context apply to all nested contexts unless overridden:

```nginx
http {
    gzip on;                    # applies to all servers

    server {
        gzip off;               # overrides for this server

        location /api/ {
            gzip on;            # overrides again for this location
        }
    }
}
```

## Config Management Commands

```bash
# Test config syntax
nginx -t

# Test and dump resolved config
nginx -T

# Reload config (graceful — no downtime)
nginx -s reload

# Check which config file is in use
nginx -V 2>&1 | grep 'conf-path'

# Enable a site (Debian/Ubuntu)
ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/mysite /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
nginx -t && nginx -s reload

# Disable a site
rm /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/mysite
nginx -t && nginx -s reload
```

## Common Directives Reference

| Directive | Context | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|----------|
| `listen` | server | Port and address to bind |
| `server_name` | server | Hostname matching |
| `root` | http, server, location | Document root |
| `index` | http, server, location | Default index files |
| `try_files` | server, location | Check files in order |
| `error_page` | http, server, location | Custom error pages |
| `return` | server, location | Return status code or redirect |
| `rewrite` | server, location | URL rewriting |
| `include` | any | Include other config files |
| `deny` / `allow` | http, server, location | IP-based access control |
| `client_max_body_size` | http, server, location | Max upload size (default 1m) |
| `sendfile` | http, server, location | Efficient file transfer |
| `gzip` | http, server, location | Response compression |
